25:04.028 --> 25:06.617
Oh, so you didn't, uh...

25:06.640 --> 25:07.821
Did you not...

25:08.789 --> 25:09.929
No, I did.

25:09.987 --> 25:14.005
You just, um, didn't
really seem as with me.

25:16.298 --> 25:17.498
I'm sorry.

25:18.240 --> 25:20.615
I... I just think that, um...

25:20.641 --> 25:21.866
Is it Nick?

25:23.446 --> 25:25.686
You must be worried
with him still out there.

25:26.779 --> 25:29.940
Oh, no, I mean, they
probably found him by now.

25:30.113 --> 25:32.878
That must've been scary,
the whole lockdown.

25:36.801 --> 25:37.983
Yeah.

25:55.739 --> 25:57.451
- There you are.
- (chuckles)

26:01.298 --> 26:02.498
Oh, my god.

26:06.708 --> 26:08.145
So where is everyone?

26:09.034 --> 26:11.324
Um, Lena and Jude went to

26:11.364 --> 26:14.643
drop Jesus at practice
and Stef's out somewhere.

26:14.718 --> 26:15.307
(line beeps)

26:15.355 --> 26:17.347
Hello, my name's Andrew.
How can I help you?

26:17.468 --> 26:19.941
Hi, my name's Justina Marks.

26:19.944 --> 26:23.030
I'm the chief admin
officer on Fost and Found,

26:23.421 --> 26:28.028
and I was hacked and I lost all
my info, including my passwords,

26:28.059 --> 26:29.919
so I can't get into my domain.

26:29.941 --> 26:31.171
Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.

26:31.207 --> 26:33.223
Uh, I can send a link
to reset your password,

26:33.259 --> 26:35.090
I just need to ask you
a few security questions.

26:35.141 --> 26:35.875
Great.

26:36.288 --> 26:37.482
Mother's maiden name?

26:37.603 --> 26:38.711
Wimberley.

26:38.830 --> 26:39.859
Place of birth?

26:39.980 --> 26:41.130
Evanston, Illinois.

26:41.165 --> 26:42.780
- No.
- No?

26:43.516 --> 26:44.445
Um...

26:45.820 --> 26:47.127
Are you sure? I mean,

26:47.248 --> 26:48.503
that's where I was born.

26:48.548 --> 26:50.488
Oh, not you, your mother's place of birth.

26:50.537 --> 26:52.532
Oh, right, sorry.

26:52.573 --> 26:54.614
Uh, yeah, it's Piggot, Arkansas.

26:54.648 --> 26:57.442
Great. Last question, favorite pet's name?

26:59.040 --> 27:00.294
Um...

27:00.917 --> 27:03.250
uh, sorry, I have so many pets.

27:03.280 --> 27:04.544
Oh yeah, what do you have?

27:04.627 --> 27:07.354
Um, I have a cat

27:07.912 --> 27:09.143
and a dog,

27:09.461 --> 27:10.452
um...

27:11.250 --> 27:14.185
I have a bird, um, a fish.

27:14.199 --> 27:15.182
Uh-huh.

27:15.301 --> 27:18.147
Um, and a snake.

27:18.201 --> 27:20.401
- You have a snake?
- Yep.

27:20.905 --> 27:22.060
(phone chimes)

27:23.299 --> 27:24.184
Buttons.

27:24.229 --> 27:25.773
Sorry, not the snake.

27:25.782 --> 27:28.061
The schnoodle.

27:28.097 --> 27:30.425
Aww. What's your snake's name?

27:31.440 --> 27:32.683
Snakey.

27:32.901 --> 27:33.967
So cute.

27:34.050 --> 27:37.751
Okay, I'll send the link to
your email, Jmarks@JMI.vox.

27:37.923 --> 27:40.182
Actually, um, no,

27:40.224 --> 27:41.223
just 'cause I was hacked,

27:41.226 --> 27:43.988
could you send it to my assistant's email?

27:44.006 --> 27:48.122
It's JP123@mymail.vox.

27:48.131 --> 27:49.148
Okay, will do.

27:49.362 --> 27:51.278
- Great, thank you so much.
- Uh-huh.

27:53.204 --> 27:54.677
Snakey the snake?

27:55.089 --> 27:56.780
I don't know what you name a snake, okay?

27:57.419 --> 27:59.888
You are pretty adorable
when you're under pressure.

28:00.009 --> 28:02.864
Okay, try to control
yourselves until I do this,

28:03.270 --> 28:04.771
then I'll leave you alone.

28:04.803 --> 28:06.250
What exactly are you doing,

28:06.701 --> 28:07.878
and am I gonna get arrested

28:07.892 --> 28:09.445
for letting you hack
somebody on my computer?

28:09.459 --> 28:10.787
We're not hacking anyone.

28:10.788 --> 28:13.079
We're simply re-routing all of
the traffic from Fost and Found

28:13.092 --> 28:14.922
to a website called Justice4Jack.

28:15.325 --> 28:16.834
I made up the name.

28:16.993 --> 28:19.028
Of course, it's not as
good as Snakey the snake.

28:19.080 --> 28:20.717
And what's on Justice4Jack?

28:20.907 --> 28:24.432
A copy of the check that
Arbiter wrote to Justina.

28:25.353 --> 28:27.884
You know, the for-profit organization that

28:27.929 --> 28:30.097
had Jack placed with
Pearson and got him killed.

28:30.097 --> 28:31.421
Uh-huh.

28:31.674 --> 28:33.056
And how'd you get this check?

28:33.929 --> 28:35.516
I would rather not say.

28:35.556 --> 28:37.336
What if they trace this back to you guys?

28:37.849 --> 28:40.013
They won't. I'm using an anonymizer.

28:40.275 --> 28:41.376
And we're gonna send the link

28:41.425 --> 28:44.484
to every lawmaker in San
Diego County and Sacramento

28:44.528 --> 28:46.848
- to kill Justina's bill.
- All right.

28:47.313 --> 28:49.209
All I have to do is press "Return".

28:49.460 --> 28:50.644
Do it.

28:51.896 --> 28:53.423
(computer beeps)

28:53.542 --> 28:55.558
(both sigh)

28:55.979 --> 28:57.307
So now what?

28:57.634 --> 29:00.001
Now we wait and see.

29:01.972 --> 29:04.363
Well, I'm exhausted.

29:04.401 --> 29:07.215
- I'm gonna try to take a nap.
- Hey, thank you.

29:07.336 --> 29:08.978
No problem.

29:14.540 --> 29:16.483
(groans)

29:20.892 --> 29:22.336
How'd you find me?

29:22.377 --> 29:23.858
The address from your desk.

29:23.861 --> 29:25.601
I can't believe you
went through my things.

29:25.640 --> 29:27.619
I can't believe that you
blatantly disobeyed me.

29:27.636 --> 29:29.878
Disobeyed? I'm not a kid anymore.

29:29.950 --> 29:31.605
18 does not make you an adult, Brandon.

29:31.637 --> 29:32.835
I can vote.

29:33.551 --> 29:35.311
Any idiot can vote.

29:35.756 --> 29:38.282
And as long as you are
eating my food under my roof,

29:38.333 --> 29:40.873
- you will obey my rules.
- She wasn't adopted yet.

29:41.154 --> 29:44.240
- Okay, I'm gonna not talking about this here.
- No, Mom, I'm sorry.

29:44.359 --> 29:45.681
We made a mistake.

29:46.029 --> 29:48.875
But we are not real brother and sister.

29:48.902 --> 29:50.391
Oh, well, what about Jesus and Mariana?

29:50.423 --> 29:51.663
Are they not your real brother and sister?

29:51.672 --> 29:52.930
No, no, that's different.
We grew up together.

29:52.970 --> 29:54.806
Callie's only been living
with us for like a year.

29:54.815 --> 29:56.195
Okay, I'm not gonna listen to this, B.

29:56.227 --> 29:57.910
- Right, 'cause you never listen.
- Okay.

29:57.967 --> 30:00.623
Just like when I try to tell you
that I was in love with Callie,

30:00.647 --> 30:01.734
you took out a restraining order.

30:01.760 --> 30:03.801
Yes, which you apparently
violated several times.

30:03.836 --> 30:05.878
- Did you not?
- This is why we don't tell you anything,

30:06.127 --> 30:08.003
because we knew you
would never understand.

30:08.124 --> 30:10.205
What's to understand, Brandon?

30:10.326 --> 30:12.540
That you had sex with your foster sister?

30:12.568 --> 30:14.394
Doesn't matter that
she wasn't adopted yet.

30:14.400 --> 30:15.340
It was wrong.

30:15.461 --> 30:17.255
That's why you didn't come
to us, because it was wrong.

30:17.294 --> 30:18.842
You knew it and you were scared.

30:18.864 --> 30:20.224
- Yeah, we were scared.
- Yeah.

30:20.269 --> 30:23.102
- We were scared to hurt the family.
- Oh, come on.

30:23.136 --> 30:25.950
We gave up everything we felt
for each other to protect you.

30:25.950 --> 30:28.618
You deceived us. You deceived us, Brandon.

30:28.673 --> 30:30.258
There is no excuse for that.

30:30.377 --> 30:31.786
And I hold you mostly responsible

30:31.807 --> 30:34.339
because Callie was vulnerable
and you, of all people,

30:34.356 --> 30:37.039
should have known better. Now,
go get the rest of your stuff

30:37.075 --> 30:39.452
-  and get home, please.
- (scoffs)

30:41.307 --> 30:43.601
You know, okay.

30:44.384 --> 30:46.605
I take full responsibility.

30:47.176 --> 30:48.988
For everything.

30:49.814 --> 30:51.431
But I'm not coming home.

30:52.816 --> 30:54.171
Okay.

30:54.844 --> 30:57.232
Well, that's great. Then
what are you gonna do, B?

30:57.313 --> 30:58.760
Are you gonna go live with your dad again?

30:58.788 --> 31:01.810
- That went really well the first time.
- No, Mom, I'm gonna live here

31:02.133 --> 31:03.278
with Cortney.

31:06.780 --> 31:08.644
You might not think I'm an adult yet,

31:08.648 --> 31:10.520
but legally, I can live wherever I want.

31:17.657 --> 31:19.040
Okay.

31:21.376 --> 31:23.146
Well, good luck with that.

31:39.232 --> 31:40.362
Shh-shh.

31:40.893 --> 31:42.304
Don't scream, don't scream.

31:42.314 --> 31:44.201
Don't scream. Okay? Just don't be scared.

31:44.233 --> 31:46.248
Don't be scared. I just wanna talk to you.

31:46.413 --> 31:48.844
I've been waiting to talk to you,

31:48.963 --> 31:50.905
so, uh, just, um...

31:50.941 --> 31:52.772
Shh.

31:55.689 --> 31:56.645
Lena: Hey.

31:57.526 --> 31:59.732
AJ, is Mike here?

31:59.853 --> 32:01.670
Uh, no.

32:02.059 --> 32:03.623
Uh, I just... I borrowed his car.

32:03.932 --> 32:05.713
And I should be going

32:05.752 --> 32:08.645
because he actually has
to get to work tonight.

32:08.811 --> 32:10.781
So I'll talk to you later?

32:12.502 --> 32:14.487
I hope you weren't on Fost and Found.

32:14.521 --> 32:15.855
Why?

32:16.751 --> 32:19.590
Because we took your
computers away for a reason.

32:22.130 --> 32:23.684
What's in there?

32:25.066 --> 32:26.365
Jack's ashes.

32:27.906 --> 32:31.636
I need you to understand why.

32:31.757 --> 32:34.592
Okay? Why... why I can't,
um... why I can't because...

32:34.618 --> 32:36.876
there's too many voices in my head.

32:36.903 --> 32:40.988
I can't, uh, think straight
because they won't stop talking.

32:41.026 --> 32:42.759
And I hate it, and I hate everything.

32:42.769 --> 32:45.200
I hate myself, and I... I hate you.

32:45.453 --> 32:48.923
You know? I hate you.

32:51.511 --> 32:53.045
What are you going to do with them?

32:54.151 --> 32:56.194
I... I don't know.

32:56.230 --> 32:59.855
Do you think we could bury
them under Frankie's tree?

33:00.167 --> 33:03.601
- Jude...
- Oh, no, that's okay.

33:03.673 --> 33:06.557
Um, I think that would
be a lovely idea, honey.

33:07.498 --> 33:08.886
(door opens)

33:09.007 --> 33:10.092
(footsteps approaching)

33:10.303 --> 33:11.460
Hey, where have you been?

33:11.464 --> 33:14.262
Uh, do you think you guys could
give us a minute alone, please?

33:14.762 --> 33:16.074
- Sure.
- Okay.

33:18.086 --> 33:19.288
(sighs)

33:19.980 --> 33:21.170
What's the matter?

33:21.221 --> 33:22.508
Apparently, Brandon has decided

33:22.525 --> 33:24.356
that he's moving in with Cortney.

33:25.784 --> 33:27.058
Did you go over there?

33:28.496 --> 33:29.785
Stef?

33:29.955 --> 33:34.046
I need to do something
to make the hurt go away.

33:35.298 --> 33:38.338
You know, I can still hear
the snap of his belt. Snap.

33:38.361 --> 33:40.895
I would beg him not to hit me,

33:40.917 --> 33:42.567
and you know what he would say?

33:42.633 --> 33:44.597
He would say, "This is gonna hurt me

33:44.625 --> 33:47.104
a lot more than it's gonna hurt you."

33:47.132 --> 33:49.688
I mean, what?

33:52.086 --> 33:53.964
He humiliated me...

33:55.730 --> 33:57.373
like you did.

34:00.183 --> 34:02.294
Please, don't hurt me.

34:04.298 --> 34:06.104
I'm not gonna hurt you.

34:10.405 --> 34:11.777
No, Nick, don't.

34:12.369 --> 34:13.791
Were you scared

34:14.985 --> 34:16.224
during the lockdown?

34:16.844 --> 34:18.344
Yeah.

34:19.224 --> 34:20.525
Were you?

34:23.251 --> 34:24.690
I texted Connor.

34:26.577 --> 34:28.204
I mean, that's okay.

34:29.045 --> 34:30.501
I miss him.

34:32.659 --> 34:33.927
I know.

34:35.295 --> 34:37.108
I miss Jack, too.

34:38.840 --> 34:40.931
Why do bad things keep happening?

34:42.170 --> 34:45.469
Nick, don't. Please, don't hurt yourself.

34:45.496 --> 34:47.045
Why? Why, huh?

34:47.056 --> 34:49.503
- I'm all alone, I have no one.
- You have me.

34:49.518 --> 34:51.190
- No, I don't.
- Yes, you do.

34:51.217 --> 34:52.784
You have me.

34:53.143 --> 34:54.693
No, I can't. I can't.

34:55.224 --> 34:56.846
Yes, you can. You can.

34:56.862 --> 34:58.152
You just have to put the gun down.

34:58.206 --> 34:59.170
What did you expect?

34:59.237 --> 35:01.161
You practically dragged him
out of his girlfriend's bed.

35:01.166 --> 35:03.057
- He was embarrassed.
